org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.engines.chunkdb.index

Class DocumentChunkIndexData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.chronos.chronodb.internal.impl.engines.chunkdb.index.DocumentChunkIndexData

  • public class DocumentChunkIndexData
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the in-memory representation of the data that is persisted inside an index chunk file.

    The primary content of this class is a list of index documents, alongside a bit of metadata (e.g. the indexers and the branch name). Note that this is a bare-bones data class; operations do not perform any consistency-insuring tasks.

    It provides two static methods for loading and persisting instances from/to a file.

      • persistToFile

        public static void persistToFile(java.io.File file,
                                 DocumentChunkIndexData chunkIndexData)
        Writes the given chunk index data into the given file.
        Parameters:
        file - The file to write the data into. Must not be null. Must refer to a file (not a directory) and must be writable. It will be fully overwritten!
        chunkIndexData - The data to write into the file. Must not be null.
        Throws:
        org.chronos.common.exceptions.ChronosIOException - thrown if the writing process failed for any reason.

      • loadFromFile

        public static DocumentChunkIndexData loadFromFile(java.io.File file)
        Attempts to load the DocumentChunkIndexData contained in the given file.
        Parameters:
        file - The file to read. Must not be null. Must point to an existing file (not a directory) that is readable.
        Returns:
        The index data object, or null if the file could not be read or is corrupted.
